Document: ParticleProcessMaterial2D
Path: godot/tutorials/2d/particle_process_material_2d.rst
Summary: Explains the Velocity property of the ParticleProcessMaterial2D in Godot Engine.

Velocity
The velocity property allows you to control the initial speed and direction of particles.

.. rst-class:: class-properties

.. rst-table::
   :widths: 20 20 60

   * - Name
     - Type
     - Description
   * - `linear`
     - :ref:`Vector3<class_Vector3>`
     - The linear velocity of the particle.
   * - `angular`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The angular velocity of the particle.
   * - `radial_accel`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The radial acceleration of the particle.
   * - `tangential_accel`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The tangential acceleration of the particle.
   * - `damping`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The damping factor of the particle.
   * - `initial_linear_velocity`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The initial linear velocity of the particle.
   * - `initial_angular_velocity`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The initial angular velocity of the particle.
   * - `initial_radial_accel`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The initial radial acceleration of the particle.
   * - `initial_tangential_accel`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The initial tangential acceleration of the particle.
   * - `initial_damping`
     - :ref:`float<class_float>`
     - The initial damping factor of the particle.

The `linear` property defines the initial velocity vector for each particle. This determines both the speed and direction in which the particle will start moving.

The `angular` property sets the initial rotational speed of the particle. Particles will rotate around their own axis at this rate.

`radial_accel` controls acceleration directed away from or towards the particle's origin. A positive value will push particles outwards, while a negative value will pull them inwards.

`tangential_accel` controls acceleration perpendicular to the particle's velocity, along the direction of its movement. This can be used to make particles curve or spiral.

`damping` reduces the particle's velocity over time. A higher damping value means the particle will slow down more quickly.

The `initial_` prefixed properties allow you to set these values at the moment of particle emission, overriding the base properties for the initial state. This provides finer control over how particles behave right from their creation.
---CHUNK---
