Summary: Explains the 'Direction' property of a 2D particle process material and its interaction with initial velocity and gravity.
Direction: This is the base direction at which particles emit. The default is Vector3(1, 0, 0) which makes particles emit to the right. However, with the default gravity settings, particles will go straight down. For this property to be noticeable, you need an initial velocity greater than 0. Setting the initial velocity to 40 makes particles emit toward the right, then go down because of gravity.
---CHUNK---
